<p>I want to make a custom filter which does a regex match on the data field from a bunch of events.  I'm working on a custom view, and editing the XML source of the custom view properties.</p>  <ul> <li>Environment: Microsoft windows server 2012 standard</li> <li>Program: event viewer</li> </ul>  <p>The events look like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;Event xmlns="http://blahblah.com"&gt;   &lt;EventData&gt;   &lt;Data&gt;Blah smith blah   &lt;/Data&gt;   &lt;/EventData&gt; &lt;/Event&gt; </code></pre>  <p>And I want to do the regex on the Data field.</p>  <p>I've tried a lot of things like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;QueryList&gt;   &lt;Query Id="0" Path=""&gt;     &lt;Select Path=""&gt;        *[EventData[Data=regex("*smith*")]]     &lt;/Select&gt;   &lt;/Query&gt; &lt;/QueryList&gt; </code></pre>  <p>as well as other lines like</p>  <pre><code>*[EventData[Data="%smith%")]] *[EventData[Data="%%smith%%")]] </code></pre>  <p>And usually get either no result, or an error for invalid xpath.</p>  <p>How can I do this?  I'd also be interested in just knowing what the context of where I am is?  Is this real xpath, or does it have some specific Microsoft version name?  How can I even get a list of the namespace that exists from within the *Event line?  I don't think it's regular xpath.</p>